history.content: 186 has spaces now in a number of discussion sections.  Majors who want to take the class should pick an open discussion section and sign up asap.  It will not be too many days longer that major priority is extended.

children.subject: Do you know if this applies to people who were affected by the CS declaration glitch? (i.e. the one where we declared but CalCentral's enrollment system is still treating us as undeclared?)
Think MDS is trying to figure it out.
Hi I recently declared CS but am still on the waitlist for 186. Is there anything I should do (drop and re-enroll, wait it out, etc.)? Thanks in advance!

Original poster speaking - I don't have the option of dropping and re-enrolling to snag the major priority spots, because when I enroll I have a time conflict with the lecture and have to wait for an override conflict to process to enroll.

Last time I tried that, it took so long to process the override that I ended up far on the waitlist for the open section I originally chose. What should I do?
If I'm declared and I'm waitlisted for a discussion section with enough available seats to let me in, can I get in?

history.content:
I enrolled for 186 when it was an open class/open discussion section but there was a conflict, so I filled out the override conflict form immediately.

After 24 hours, the conflict form hadn't processed (though it should have since I only had 10 units and the section was open), so I emailed SIS with a support ticket, and after more than a week, they got around to my support ticket and put me on the waitlist - now am at position #184.  But there had been no waitlist for the class when I submitted the form.

Will people who got put really far back on the waitlist due to the system having issues really not be able to get into the class? Is the waitlist being processed manually, or is the class really closed?
history.subject: will 186 expand for waitlisted students (esp if enrolled when class was open)
